@node history "Shades.guide v1.5"

   Program history & future


   v1.0  Basic operation: gui, cx_broker, dimmer, error handling
   v1.0a Debugging raw version
   v1.1  Added icon & tooltypes, improved screen color loading
   v1.2  Added color-to-dim selection (changed that in 1.4)
   v1.2a Improved error & hotkey handling, cleaned up code
   v1.3  Added test for palette change by other program;
         added color depth computing
   v1.3a Cleaned up code
   v1.4  Changed color selection gadget form slider to palette;
         first official release.
   v1.5  Recompiled with EasyGui3.3a:
         changed palette gadget better reflects selected color.
         Oops: forgot to FreeScreenDrawInfo()

   Shades v1.5 is tested on the following system:
   - Amiga 4000/40, 16 Mb RAM, Fastlane z3, Retina Z2, ZIP-drive, 12 speed CD-ROM

   Please let me know if it works on your system as well. 
   Send your reply to @{" me " link author}.

   Known bugs
   Opening Shades while running Professional Page 4.1 under Workbench 3.1
   will guru your system: PPage 4.1 is badly broken under WB 3.1! (It ain't 
   me, mum).
   If you find any other bugs, please report.

   Future
   1. Autodetect background color

   Shades works fine for me right now, so I will only do the above
   if I get some respons...

   Read on @{" Begin " link main}
@endnode

